div.p:
On the proposal of Baron d’Itajuba, as one of the arbitrators, the
                            tribunal decided to require a written or printed statement or argument
                            from the counsel of Great Britain upon the following questions of law: 
                                1.

The question of due diligence, generally considered;
                                2.

The special question, as to the effect of the commissions of
                                    confederate ships of war entering British ports;
                                3.

The special question, as to supplies of coal in British ports
                                    to confederate ships;
